    "body": "**Description of the problem**\r\n\r\n_The bug was first reported by https://github.com/maihao14 in https://github.com/GenericMappingTools/pygmt/issues/1461._\r\n\r\n**Full script that generated the error**\r\n\r\n```\r\ngmt begin map\r\ngmt basemap -R0/10/0/10 -JX10c -Baf -Y20c\r\nfor i in $(seq 1 65); do\r\n\techo 5 5 | gmt plot -Sc0.2c -Gred -lPoint$i\r\ndone\r\ngmt end show\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt works for 64 legend entries but crashes for >=65 entries.\r\n\r\nIf the maximum number of allowed entries is 64, we should:\r\n\r\n1. Document the number in the **-l** option explanation\r\n2. Return an error or a warning (truncated to the first 64 entries) if more than 64 entries are given\r\n\r\n**System information**\r\n\r\n* GMT version (`gmt --version`): 6.3.0_c12a98f_2021.08.21\r\n",
